# CIAM Touch RFID Button v3

IoT device firmware for an ESP8266-based (WeMos D1 mini) RFID and capacitive touch button reader that publishes events to a Flatbox cloud platform via MQTT.

**Firmware Version:** V6.00 | **Hardware Version:** V3.00

## Features

- RFID card reading via SoftwareSerial (9600 baud) with frame validation
- Capacitive touch button detection
- MQTT event publishing to Flatbox IoT platform (JSON format) with truncation detection
- WiFi configuration portal via WiFiManager (on-demand)
- OTA (Over-the-Air) firmware updates (password-protected)
- NTP time synchronization (5-retry cap on startup and resync)
- RGB LED and piezo buzzer feedback
- Device health monitoring (WiFi RSSI, message counters, battery voltage)
- MQTT connect safeguard: 4 retries then WiFiManager fallback for config correction
- Automatic restart on persistent MQTT failures (configurable threshold, default 150)
- LittleFS-based persistent configuration storage (MQTT, NTP, Device_ID all configurable)
- Remote RGB LED control via MQTT (RGB values, hex color, on/off)
- Remote buzzer activation via MQTT (configurable duration)
- Remote parameter update via MQTT (publish interval, thresholds, tone/flash durations, OTA trigger)
- WiFi SSID and installation location reported in heartbeat payload
- Fallback WiFi support (secondary SSID/password tried if primary network fails)
- Remote WiFi credential push via MQTT (stored as fallback, used on next reconnect)
- Installation location configurable via WiFiManager portal and remotely via MQTT
- MQTT Last Will and Testament (LWT) for instant offline detection
- Retained heartbeat messages so dashboard gets state immediately
- Monotonic message sequence numbers on all MQTT publishes (gap detection)
- Boot reason reporting in heartbeat (`ESP.getResetReason()`)
- Hardware watchdog timer (8s timeout, auto-fed in loop)
- Non-blocking remote buzzer (millis-based, FSM keeps running during long beeps)
- Exponential backoff on MQTT reconnect (3s to 60s cap)
- RFID rate limiting (same card max once per 60s to prevent flooding)
- Config schema versioning with automatic migration
- XOR obfuscation of MQTT password in LittleFS (deters casual flash extraction)

## Hardware

| Pin | Function         | Component             |
|-----|------------------|-----------------------|
| D0  | Touch Button     | Capacitive Touch Pad  |
| D2  | RFID TX          | RFID Reader (SSerial) |
| D3  | RFID RX          | RFID Reader (SSerial) |
| D4  | RGB Purple       | RGB LED               |
| D5  | Buzzer           | Piezo Buzzer          |
| D6  | RGB Blue/White   | RGB LED               |
| D7  | RGB Green/White  | RGB LED               |
| D8  | RGB Red/White    | RGB LED               |
| A0  | Battery Voltage  | Battery Monitor       |

## Project Structure

```
├── include/
│   └── Settings.h              # Compile-time constants (extern declarations)
├── lib/
│   ├── Buzzer/src/             # BTN_Bzzr - piezo buzzer control
│   ├── Flatbox_publish/src/    # flatbox - MQTT JSON payload formatting
│   ├── NTP_Client/src/         # NTPClient - UDP time synchronization
│   ├── RGB/src/                # BlinkRGB / BlinkColor - LED control (digital + PWM)
│   ├── TimeESP/src/            # TimeLibEsp - date/time management
│   └── TouchBtn/src/           # TouchPadButton - capacitive input
├── src/
│   ├── main.cpp                # FSM, setup, loop, sensor read/publish
│   ├── pins.h                  # Centralized pin definitions
│   ├── feedback.h/.cpp         # LED + buzzer abstraction layer
│   ├── config.h/.cpp           # BtnConf struct, LittleFS read/save, XOR obfuscation
│   ├── ota.h/.cpp              # OTA update mode
│   ├── wifi_setup.h/.cpp       # WiFiManager portals, fallback WiFi
│   ├── mqtt_manager.h/.cpp     # MQTT connect/reconnect, callback dispatch, subscriptions
│   └── Settings.cpp            # Definitions for Settings.h constants and runtime vars
└── platformio.ini              # Build configuration (espressif8266, d1_mini)
```

## Finite State Machine

The firmware runs a priority-based finite state machine with 7 states. Event priority is **card > button > timers** -- higher-priority events preempt lower-priority checks within the IDLE state.

### State Diagram

```
                         ┌──────────────────────────────────────────┐
                         │              STARTUP                     │
                         │  Load config, WiFi connect, NTP sync     │
                         └──────────────┬───────────────────────────┘
                                        │
                          ┌─────────────▼─────────────┐
            ┌────────────►│         IDLE (0)           │◄───────────────────────┐
            │             │                            │                        │
            │             │  1. readTag()  ─────────┐  │                        │
            │             │  2. readBtn()  ────────┐│  │                        │
            │             │  3. checkalarms()      ││  │                        │
            │             │  4. 30min timer ──┐    ││  │                        │
            │             │  5. 60min timer ┐ │    ││  │                        │
            │             │  6. MQTT keepalive │    ││  │                        │
            │             └──┬──────┬───────┼─┼────┼┼──┘                        │
            │                │      │       │ │    ││                            │
            │   ┌────────────┘      │       │ │    │└───────────────┐            │
            │   │  ┌────────────────┘       │ │    │                │            │
            │   │  │  ┌─────────────────────┘ │    │                │            │
            │   │  │  │  ┌────────────────────┘    │                │            │
            │   │  │  │  │                         │                │            │
            │   ▼  ▼  ▼  ▼                         ▼                ▼            │
            │  ┌────────────┐              ┌──────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐     │
            │  │UPDATE_TIME │              │ TRANSMIT     │  │ TRANSMIT    │     │
            │  │   (6)      │              │ BOTON_DATA   │  │ CARD_DATA   │     │
            │  │            │              │   (1)        │  │   (2)       │     │
            │  │ NTP sync   │              │              │  │             │     │
            │  │ (5 retries)│              │ MQTT check   │  │ MQTT check  │     │
            │  └─────┬──────┘              │ CheckTime()  │  │ CheckTime() │     │
            │        │                     │ publish_Boton │  │ publishRFID │     │
            │        └──────►IDLE          └──────┬───────┘  └──────┬──────┘     │
            │                                     │                 │            │
            │                                     └──────►IDLE◄────┘            │
            │                                                                   │
            │  ┌────────────┐                                                   │
            │  │ UPDATE (3) │                                                   │
            │  │            │                                                   │
            │  │ updateDev  │                                                   │
            │  │ Info()     │                                                   │
            │  │ (sets msg  │                                                   │
            │  │  "on" or   │                                                   │
            │  │  "LOWiFi") │                                                   │
            │  └──────┬─────┘                                                   │
            │         │ always                                                  │
            │         ▼                                                         │
            │  ┌──────────────────┐                                             │
            │  │ TRANSMIT_DEVICE  │                                             │
            │  │ UPDATE (5)       │─────────────────────────────────────────────┘
            │  │                  │
            │  │ MQTT check       │
            │  │ CheckTime()      │
            │  │ publishRF_ID_    │
            │  │ Manejo()         │
            │  └──────────────────┘
            │
            │  ┌──────────────────┐
            │  │ RDY_TO_UPDATE    │   (entered from startup only,
            │  │ OTA (7)          │    loops indefinitely)
            │  │                  │
            │  │ ArduinoOTA       │
            │  │ .handle()        │
            │  └──────────────────┘
```

### State Transition Summary

| From State | To State | Trigger |
| --- | --- | --- |
| IDLE | TRANSMIT_CARD_DATA | RFID card detected by `readTag()` (non-duplicate) |
| IDLE | TRANSMIT_BOTON_DATA | Button press detected by `readBtn()` |
| IDLE | UPDATE | 30-minute periodic timer expires |
| IDLE | UPDATE_TIME | 60-minute NTP resync timer expires |
| IDLE | (restart) | Failed MQTT messages exceed threshold (150) |
| TRANSMIT_BOTON_DATA | IDLE | After publishing button event |
| TRANSMIT_CARD_DATA | IDLE | After publishing card event |
| UPDATE | TRANSMIT_DEVICE_UPDATE | Always (msg carries "on" or "LOWiFi") |
| TRANSMIT_DEVICE_UPDATE | IDLE | After publishing device data |
| UPDATE_TIME | IDLE | After NTP sync (up to 5 retries) |
| RDY_TO_UPDATE_OTA | RDY_TO_UPDATE_OTA | Loops waiting for OTA upload |
| (any unknown) | IDLE | Default handler resets to IDLE |

## MQTT Communication

- **Broker:** Configurable via WiFiManager (default: `172.18.98.142:1883`)
- **Auth:** Username + password (configurable via WiFiManager)
- **Transport:** Plaintext TCP (no TLS)
- **Publish topic:** `iot-2/evt/status/fmt/json`
- **Subscribe topics:** Device management, response, update, reboot, and control channels

### Event Payload Example

```json
{
  "d": {
    "botondata": {
      "ChipID": "782184",
      "IDEventoBoton": "782184-1",
      "Tstamp": "2026-03-05T17:17:56"
    }
  }
}
```

### Subscribe Topics

| Topic | Purpose |
| ------- | --------- |
| `iotdm-1/response/` | Server acknowledgment messages (logged to serial) |
| `iotdm-1/device/update` | Remote parameter updates (see table below) |
| `iotdm-1/mgmt/initiate/device/reboot` | Remote reboot (any payload triggers `ESP.reset()`) |
| `iotdm-1/device/ctrl` | RGB LED and buzzer control |

### Remote Control Commands (`iotdm-1/device/ctrl`)

**RGB color (0-255 per channel, PWM):**

```json
{"r": 255, "g": 128, "b": 0}
```

**Hex color (with or without `#`):**

```json
{"hex": "#FF8000"}
```

**On/Off (all channels max or off):**

```json
{"cmd": "on"}
{"cmd": "off"}
```

**Buzzer activation (duration in seconds, 1-300):**

```json
{"beep": 5}
{"beep": "60"}
```

Note: The buzzer command is blocking -- the device will not process other MQTT messages until the beep completes.

### Remote Parameter Updates (`iotdm-1/device/update`)

All parameters are optional -- include only the ones you want to change. Multiple parameters can be sent in a single message. Changes are **runtime only** and reset to defaults on reboot.

```json
{"publish_interval": 2000, "fail_threshold": 100, "rssi_threshold": -80}
```

| JSON Key | Type | Default | What it controls |
| ---------- | ------ | --------- | ----------------- |
| `publish_interval` | unsigned long | 1000 | Base time unit (ms) -- affects publish rate, NTP resync (60x), device update (30x), hourly reset (3600x) |
| `btn_hold_time` | unsigned long | 2000 | Button hold duration (ms) for entering config/OTA mode at startup |
| `tono_corto` | unsigned long | 250 | Short beep duration (ms) |
| `tono_medio` | unsigned long | 500 | Medium beep duration (ms) |
| `tono_largo` | unsigned long | 1000 | Long beep duration (ms) |
| `flash_corto` | unsigned long | 250 | Short LED flash duration (ms) |
| `flash_medio` | unsigned long | 500 | Medium LED flash duration (ms) |
| `flash_largo` | unsigned long | 1000 | Long LED flash duration (ms) |
| `fail_threshold` | int | 150 | MQTT publish failures before auto-reboot |
| `rssi_threshold` | int | -75 | WiFi signal alarm threshold (dBm) |
| `heartbeat_minutes` | int | 30 | Heartbeat interval in minutes (1-1440) |
| `location` | string | -- | Installation location (saved to LittleFS) |
| `wifi_ssid` + `wifi_pass` | string | -- | Push new WiFi credentials (stored as fallback) |
| `fallback_ssid` + `fallback_pass` | string | -- | Set/update fallback WiFi network |
| `ota` | bool | -- | Set `true` to trigger OTA mode remotely |

Current parameter values are reported in the `manageTopic` metadata payload on device startup.

## Configuration (LittleFS)

Stored as `/config.json` on the device flash:

| Parameter             | Default              |
|-----------------------|----------------------|
| MQTT_Server           | 172.18.98.142        |
| MQTT_Port             | 1883                 |
| MQTT_User             | esp8266              |
| MQTT_Password         | esp8266              |
| NTPClient_SERVER      | time-a-g.nist.gov    |
| NTPClient_interval    | 60000 (ms)           |
| Device_ID             | CIAM                 |
| Location              | (empty)              |
| Wifi_Fallback_SSID    | (empty)              |
| Wifi_Fallback_Pass    | (empty)              |

## Startup Behavior

1. Load config from LittleFS, build MQTT client ID from Device_ID
2. **First 2-second window:** Hold button to enter WiFi configuration portal
3. **Second 2-second window:** Hold button to enter OTA update mode (password-protected)
4. Otherwise: Auto-connect WiFi (if primary fails, tries fallback SSID if configured), sync NTP (5 retries max), connect MQTT (4 retries, tries fallback WiFi, then falls back to WiFiManager on failure), enter IDLE state

## Build

Requires [PlatformIO](https://platformio.org/).

```bash
# Build
pio run

# Upload via serial
pio run --target upload

# Monitor serial output
pio device monitor -b 115200
```

### OTA Upload (Over-the-Air)

1. Power on device, hold button during 2nd 2-second window (red LED on)
1. Serial shows `Starting OTA` then `Ready`
1. Connect your computer to the `RFID_OTA` WiFi AP (password: `FLATB0X_OTA`)
1. Device IP is `192.168.4.1` (ESP8266 AP default)
1. Upload firmware:

```bash
# PlatformIO CLI
pio run --target upload --upload-port 192.168.4.1 --upload-flags="--auth=FLATB0X_OTA"

# Or directly via espota.py
python espota.py -i 192.168.4.1 -p 8266 -a FLATB0X_OTA -f .pio/build/d1_mini/firmware.bin
```

1. Serial monitor shows progress (`OTA progress: 0%`...`100%`) and device reboots on completion

**OTA password:** `FLATB0X_OTA` (defined in `Settings.h`, protects both WiFi AP and upload auth)

## Dependencies

- ESP8266WiFi / WiFiUdp
- WiFiManager v2.x
- PubSubClient v2.8 (MQTT)
- ArduinoJson v7
- ArduinoOTA
- ESP8266WebServer / ESP8266mDNS / DNSServer
- LittleFS (FS)

## WiFi Resilience

The device uses a multi-layer WiFi recovery strategy:

1. **Primary WiFi** -- stored by WiFiManager in ESP8266 flash. If the AP is replaced with same SSID/password, the device reconnects automatically.
2. **Fallback WiFi** -- secondary SSID/password stored in LittleFS (`config.json`). Tried automatically if primary WiFi fails at startup or after MQTT connection failures.
3. **Remote credential push** -- send new WiFi credentials via MQTT before rotating the AP. The device stores them as fallback and will use them on next reconnect: `{"wifi_ssid": "NewNetwork", "wifi_pass": "NewPassword"}`
4. **WiFiManager portal** -- if both primary and fallback fail, the device opens the config portal for manual reconfiguration.

**Heartbeat location tracking:** The `Location` field (set during installation via WiFiManager or remotely via MQTT) is reported in every heartbeat. The dashboard can use `device_id` + `Location` + `SSID` to identify where a device is installed and detect offline devices when heartbeats stop arriving (expected interval: `heartbeat_minutes`, default 30 min).

## Known Limitations

- NTP synchronization can be slow on startup (mitigated with 5-retry loop, continues without time if all fail)
- Maximum MQTT payload buffer: 300 bytes (truncation detected and logged)
- MQTT connection is plaintext (no TLS) -- acceptable for LAN deployment, not for internet-facing brokers
- OTA credentials are stored in source code (Settings.h); MQTT credentials are in LittleFS config.json (XOR obfuscated, not encrypted)
- XOR obfuscation is NOT encryption -- it deters casual flash dump reading but not a determined attacker. TLS planned for ESP32 version.
- Short beeps (tono_corto/medio/largo) remain blocking. Only remote buzzer (`{"beep": N}`) is non-blocking.
- RFID frame validation is length-based only (no checksum verification -- reader-model-dependent)

## Changelog

### v6.00 - Modular Architecture Refactor

Codebase restructured for modularity, scalability, and extensibility. No behavior changes -- same serial output, MQTT payloads, and FSM logic. Goal: make the firmware a standard platform where sensor modules are plug-and-play.

Architecture:

- Extracted `src/pins.h` -- all hardware pin definitions centralized in one file. Changing a pin or porting to new hardware requires editing only this file.
- Extracted `src/feedback.h/.cpp` -- unified LED + buzzer abstraction layer with semantic functions (`feedback_ok()`, `feedback_error()`, `feedback_warning()`, etc.). Swapping LED hardware (e.g., WS2812) requires editing only `feedback.cpp`.
- Extracted `src/config.h/.cpp` -- `BtnConf` struct, LittleFS read/save, XOR hex obfuscation, WiFiManager parameter handling, config version migration. All config logic in one place.
- Extracted `src/ota.h/.cpp` -- OTA update mode setup isolated from main FSM.
- Extracted `src/wifi_setup.h/.cpp` -- WiFiManager portal modes (on-demand and auto) and fallback WiFi connection logic.
- Extracted `src/mqtt_manager.h/.cpp` -- MQTT connect/reconnect with LWT and exponential backoff, callback dispatcher (response/reboot/update/RGB handlers), topic subscriptions, and device metadata publishing.
- Created `src/Settings.cpp` -- definitions for all `Settings.h` extern declarations. `Settings.h` now contains only extern declarations (proper header/source split, no more globals defined in a header).
- `main.cpp` reduced from 1,245 lines to ~340 lines -- contains only FSM, setup, loop, and sensor read/publish functions.

Bug fixes:

- **CRASH FIX:** `LWT_PAYLOAD` was declared `PROGMEM` but passed to `PubSubClient::connect()` which reads via normal RAM access. On ESP8266, this caused Exception 3 (unaligned flash read) and crash loop at MQTT connect. Removed `PROGMEM` (payload is only 33 bytes).
- **BUG FIX:** XOR password obfuscation (v5.00) produced raw binary bytes that are not valid UTF-8. ArduinoJson corrupted them during JSON serialize/deserialize round-trip, making MQTT password unrecoverable after first save. Replaced with hex-encoded XOR: plaintext -> XOR each byte -> hex string (e.g., `"esp8266"` -> `"c0d6d59d979393"`). Config version bumped to v3. Devices with v2 config auto-migrate (password reset to default since binary data was unrecoverable).

### v5.00 - Pre-release Hardening

Storage migration:

- Migrated from SPIFFS to LittleFS (SPIFFS deprecated on ESP8266)

Library updates:

- ArduinoJson v5.13 -> v7 (all 8 call sites migrated to new API)
- WiFiManager v0.16 -> v2.x
- Removed incompatible SoftwareSerialEsp32 dependency (ESP8266 provides SoftwareSerial natively)
- Fixed SoftwareSerial constructor to 3-arg form (v8.x API)

FSM fixes (round 1):

- Added `default:` case to switch -- resets unknown states to IDLE with serial warning
- Fixed `checkalarms()` -- `BeepSignalWarning` only resets when RSSI is above threshold
- `STATE_UPDATE` no longer overwrites `STATE_TRANSMIT_ALARM_UPDATE` set by `updateDeviceInfo()`
- Added MQTT reconnect checks before publish in `TRANSMIT_BOTON_DATA` and `TRANSMIT_CARD_DATA`
- Added early-exit guards in IDLE to enforce event priority (card > button > timers)

FSM fixes (round 2):

- `MQTTreconnect()` capped at 3 retries per call (was infinite loop, could block 30+ seconds)
- `NormalReset()` now checks MQTT connection and calls `CheckTime()` before publishing
- `readTag()` rejects duplicate consecutive card reads early (before LED/buzzer/state change)
- RFID read delay reduced from 10ms to 2ms per byte (120ms -> 24ms total blocking)
- Merged `STATE_TRANSMIT_ALARM_UPDATE` into `STATE_TRANSMIT_DEVICE_UPDATE` (identical logic, `msg` field carries the distinction)
- Unified RSSI alarm threshold to `RSSI_LOW_THRESHOLD` constant in Settings.h (was -85 in `checkalarms()` vs -75 in `updateDeviceInfo()`)
- `failed` counter now halves on success instead of zeroing (prevents masking persistent degradation)

Library bug fixes:

- **BUG FIX:** `BlinkColor` constructor stored `pin1` into `_pin2` (third LED channel never worked)
- **BUG FIX:** `TouchPadButton._prev_Button_State` was uninitialized (could miss first button press)
- **BUG FIX:** `Flatbox_Publish.Administracion_Dispositivo` had duplicate JSON field (`publicados` and `enviados` both mapped to same value). Added `sent` parameter to differentiate published vs sent counters.
- Consolidated 3 `flatbox` instances into 1 (saved 1,828 bytes RAM -- 43.7% -> 41.5%)
- Commented out unused methods across all libraries to reduce flash/RAM footprint:
  - Buzzer: `This_Bzzr_State()`, `Change_Bzzr_State()`
  - RGB: `BlinkRGB::Change_RGB_State()`
  - NTP_Client: `getHours()`, `getMinutes()`, `getSeconds()`, `getFormattedTime()`, 3 unused constructors
  - TimeESP: `hourFormat12()`, `isAM()`, `isPM()`, `adjustTime()`, `setSyncInterval()`, entire `DateStrings.cpp`
- Fixed broken macros in TimeLibEsp.h (`minutesToTime_t`, `hoursToTime_t`, etc. had double-paren syntax)

TimeESP library rewrite:

- Rewrote lib/TimeESP from 4 files (553 lines) down to 2 files (155 lines)
- Deleted `TimeEsp.h` (redirect header), `DateStrings.cpp` (fully commented out)
- Deleted legacy files: `examples/` directory (11 sketches), `Readme.txt`, `keywords.txt`, `library.json`, `library.properties`
- Kept identical API surface -- zero changes to main.cpp required
- New `TimeLibEsp.h`: types, constants, and only the function declarations used by the project
- New `TimeESP.cpp`: clean implementations with no commented-out blocks

MQTT connection safeguard:

- `mqttConnect()` reduced from 30 retries + blind `ESP.restart()` to 4 retries + WiFiManager fallback
- On 4 failed attempts, opens on-demand WiFiManager config portal so user can correct MQTT server/port/credentials
- After saving new config, device restarts with corrected settings
- Prints PubSubClient return code (`rc=`) on each failure to aid diagnosis

Bug fixes (round 3):

- **BUG FIX:** `CheckTime()` `prevDisplay` was local (always 0), never actually skipped redundant updates. Made `static` so it persists across calls.
- **BUG FIX:** `CheckTime()` called `now()` twice per invocation -- second call could tick sysTime forward, causing 1-second timestamp skew. Now calls `now()` once and reuses the value.
- **BUG FIX:** `readTag()` never cleared `inputString` before accumulating new bytes, causing stale data to concatenate with new card reads after duplicate-guard early returns.
- **BUG FIX:** `clearBufferArray()` used `count` (already reset to 0) as loop bound, so `tagID[]` array was never actually cleared. Changed to use `DataLenght` constant.
- **BUG FIX:** `NTP_ready()` had 1500ms timeout loop with 1000ms `delay()` inside -- only 1 iteration ever ran. Reduced delay to 100ms, allowing ~14 polling iterations within the timeout.
- Fixed serial label "Servidor de MQTT" that actually printed MQTT username -- changed to "Usuario de MQTT"
- Initialized `Numero_ID_Eventos_Tarjeta = 0` explicitly (was relying on implicit BSS zeroing)
- Changed MQTT topic buffers in Settings.h from fixed sizes to compiler-sized `char[]` (eliminates over/under-sizing risk)
- Made `initManagedDevice()` 500-byte serialization buffer `static` to avoid stack pressure on ESP8266 (4KB stack)

Pre-release blocker fixes:

- **BLOCKER FIX:** `charBuf[30]` in `mqttConnect()` and `MQTTreconnect()` was too small for MQTT client ID (up to 38 chars). Increased to `charBuf[50]` to prevent truncation/buffer overflow.
- **BLOCKER FIX:** Removed hardcoded `#define TOKEN` from Settings.h (dead code, credentials stored in source)
- **BLOCKER FIX:** Added `ArduinoOTA.setPassword(password_OTA)` in `BOOT_TO_OTA()` -- OTA was previously open with no authentication
- **HIGH FIX:** NTP startup `while` loop could hang forever if NTP server was unreachable. Capped at 5 retries with serial progress output, then continues without time sync.
- **HIGH FIX:** `Flatbox_Publish` `serializeJson()` calls had no overflow detection -- if JSON exceeded 300-byte buffers, payload would be silently truncated and MQTT broker would receive invalid JSON. Added return-value checks with serial warnings on all 3 serialization methods.

Low-priority fixes:

- **BUG FIX:** `tagID[DataLenght]` was 10 bytes but `readTag()` wrote up to index 12 (13-byte RFID frame). Added `RFID_FRAME_SIZE` (13) constant and resized `tagID[]` to match.
- Added RFID frame validation in `readTag()` -- checks that card ID bytes (positions 4-7) produced a non-empty string. Discards empty/incomplete frames from noisy serial line before processing.
- Changed `FirmwareVersion` / `HardwareVersion` from `String` to `const char[]` in Settings.h (saves ~56 bytes heap)
- Moved `DEVICE_ID` from compile-time `#define` in Settings.h to runtime-configurable field in LittleFS `config.json`. Now editable via WiFiManager portal. Default remains "CIAM" for backwards compatibility.

OTA improvements:

- Added `ArduinoOTA` event handlers (`onStart`, `onEnd`, `onProgress`, `onError`) -- OTA upload now shows progress percentage, blue LED solid during transfer, triple beep on success, red flash + double beep on failure with error type logged to serial
- Wrapped OTA serial strings in `F()` macro (saves 20 bytes RAM)

Remote command infrastructure:

- Added MQTT subscribe topic `iotdm-1/device/ctrl` for RGB LED and buzzer control
- Added `BlinkRGB::SetPWM(int value)` -- per-channel PWM control (0-255 mapped to ESP8266 analogWrite 0-1023)
- Added `BlinkColor::SetRGB(int r, int g, int b)` -- full RGB color setting with correct pin mapping
- `handleRGBCommand()` parses 3 JSON formats: `{r,g,b}`, `{hex}`, `{cmd: on/off}` plus `{beep}` for buzzer
- Rewrote `handleUpdate()` -- now parses and applies 10 configurable parameters from JSON payload (was log-only)
- Added remote OTA trigger via `{"ota": true}` on update topic
- Converted `FAILTRESHOLD` and `RSSI_LOW_THRESHOLD` from `#define` to runtime variables (`fail_threshold`, `rssi_low_threshold`) so they can be changed remotely
- Updated `initManagedDevice()` metadata to report all configurable parameter values to broker on startup

WiFi resilience and device location:

- Added `Location` field to BtnConf -- configurable via WiFiManager portal and remotely via MQTT update topic, persisted in LittleFS
- Added `Wifi_Fallback_SSID` / `Wifi_Fallback_Pass` to BtnConf -- fallback WiFi credentials tried if primary network fails
- Added `tryFallbackWifi()` -- attempts connection to fallback SSID with 15s timeout before falling back to WiFiManager portal
- Added `saveConfigToLittleFS()` helper for remote config persistence (location, WiFi credential updates)
- Integrated fallback WiFi into startup WiFi loop and MQTT connect failure path
- Added `WiFi.SSID()` and `Location` to heartbeat payload (`Administracion_Dispositivo`)
- Added remote WiFi credential push via update topic (`wifi_ssid` + `wifi_pass`) -- stores as fallback for next reconnect
- Added remote fallback SSID update via update topic (`fallback_ssid` + `fallback_pass`)
- Added remote location update via update topic (`location`) -- persisted to LittleFS immediately
- Increased `_Manejo_Data` buffer from 450 to 550 bytes to accommodate SSID + Location fields
- Increased `initManagedDevice()` metadata buffer from 500 to 600 bytes

IoT best practices:

- Added MQTT Last Will and Testament (LWT) -- broker publishes `{"Msg":"offline"}` to manageTopic when device disconnects unexpectedly
- Added `retain=true` on heartbeat publish -- dashboard immediately gets last known state on connect
- Added monotonic `msg_seq` counter to all MQTT payloads (heartbeat, button, card) -- server can detect gaps and duplicates
- Added `boot_reason` field to heartbeat from `ESP.getResetReason()` -- distinguishes power cycle, watchdog, exception, OTA, remote reboot
- Added hardware watchdog timer (`ESP.wdtEnable(8000)`) with `ESP.wdtFeed()` in loop -- auto-restart on hang
- Made remote buzzer non-blocking (`BeepNonBlocking()` + `alarm.update()` in loop) -- FSM continues during long beeps
- Added exponential backoff to `MQTTreconnect()` (3s -> 6s -> 12s -> ... -> 60s cap) -- reduces reconnect storm on broker outage
- Added RFID rate limiting -- same card ID can only publish once per 60s (prevents card-left-on-reader flooding)
- Added `config_version` field to `config.json` with automatic migration -- new fields get defaults on firmware upgrade
- Added XOR obfuscation for MQTT password in LittleFS -- deters casual flash dump reading (not encryption)
- `MQTTreconnect()` now calls `initManagedDevice()` after successful reconnect to re-subscribe all topics
- Increased `_Manejo_Data` buffer from 550 to 600 bytes for seq + boot_reason fields

Code quality:

- Added include guard to Settings.h
- Added `build_flags = -DMQTT_MAX_PACKET_SIZE=512` for PubSubClient
- Pinned library versions in platformio.ini
